-- General Electric Bids $1.3 Billion for Wellstream Holdings, Times Reports
-- B y   A n d r e w   M a c A s k i l l
-- 2010-10-03T05:06:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/general-electric-bids-1-3-billion-for-wellstream-times-says.html
General Electric Co.  made a bid worth
more than 800 million pounds ($1.3 billion) for  Wellstream
Holdings Plc , the Sunday Times  reported , citing unidentified
people close to the matter.  National Oilwell Varco Inc.  is a rival bidder for the
company which makes pipes used in deep-sea drilling, the
newspaper said. Wellstream hired Rothschild & Sons Ltd. and
Credit Suisse Group AG as advisers, it said. 